							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/philipcarrgomm/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Philip-Carr-Gomm-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Philip-Carr-Gomm-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Philip Carr-Gomm" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/philipcarrgomm/">Philip Carr-Gomm</a></h6>
										Philip Carr-Gomm is a writer and psychologist. His many books include <em>Sacred Places</em> (2008), <em>Druid Mysteries</em> (2002) and <em>The Book of English Magic</em> (with Richard Heygate, 2009).																			</div>
